external_knowledge:
- "literary stars": refers to authors;
- "sailed past the thirty-review milestone": means the post received more than 30 ratings;
- "guardian of the keep": metaphor for the author named "Admin";
- "whispered about after the winter solstice of 2022": indicates the post was updated after '2022-01-01';
- "glowing reviews from the hearts of the readers": refers to the average rating.

sql:
SELECT post_id, COUNT(*) AS number_of_views
FROM post_views
GROUP BY post_id;

SELECT p.title, p.slug, p.published, a.author_name, a.email
FROM posts p
LEFT JOIN authors a ON p.author_id = a.author_id;

SELECT author_name
FROM authors
WHERE author_id NOT IN (
    SELECT author_id
    FROM posts
);

external_knowledge:
- "Sowers" refers to authors who plant "seeds" (posts) in the "garden" (blog or forum).;
- "Sprouted seeds" represent comments that grow around the original posts. The growth around each seed indicates the level of interaction or interest prompted by the post.;
- The "garden" metaphorically shows the community's engagement with the content created by different sowers.
